The paper deals with polyhedra and their extended formulations, which are topics commonly studied in computational geometry (cs.CG), combinatorial optimization (cs.CO), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the relationship between radial cones and certain faces of polyhedra, which is a topic relevant to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper uses techniques from linear programming and polyhedral combinatorics, which are areas of research in machine learning (cs.LG).
